01:36.911 --> 01:40.613
Go on ahead. Right through there.

01:59.098 --> 02:00.397
Hello?

02:08.007 --> 02:09.973
You came.

02:09.976 --> 02:11.208
Did I have a choice?

02:11.210 --> 02:12.843
You always have a choice.

02:30.062 --> 02:31.594
Come in.

02:57.286 --> 03:01.322
It's been a weird couple of days.

03:01.324 --> 03:02.757
Yeah.

03:25.012 --> 03:27.179
Hello.

03:27.181 --> 03:30.182
Did you strike a blow for
justice today, Mr. Rhoades?

03:30.184 --> 03:31.583
I do believe we did.

03:31.585 --> 03:32.852
You organized this

03:32.854 --> 03:34.419
and then made sure I wasn't
there when it happened.

03:34.421 --> 03:35.788
You're welcome.

03:35.790 --> 03:38.023
Did you consider for a second
what that was gonna do to me?

03:38.025 --> 03:39.024
Should I go?

03:39.026 --> 03:39.859
- Yes!
- Yes.

03:39.861 --> 03:42.227
Okay.

03:43.529 --> 03:45.563
My name, my absence when it happened

03:45.565 --> 03:47.198
puts me under suspicion there forever.

03:47.200 --> 03:48.767
What should I have done?

03:48.769 --> 03:52.603
Told you so that you could
be there for an arrest?

03:52.605 --> 03:55.473
And if you had been there,
you'd be even more pissed off.

03:55.475 --> 03:57.041
You don't think so, but I know it.

03:57.043 --> 03:58.441
At least then they wouldn't
think I knew it was coming.

03:58.443 --> 04:00.477
Oh, they all know it was coming.

04:00.479 --> 04:02.179
It's Judgment Day.

04:04.216 --> 04:07.217
My office is taking an
action, and there's nothing

04:07.219 --> 04:09.419
that you or anybody
there can do about it.

04:09.421 --> 04:11.922
And when that action is
finished, it will be the end.

04:11.924 --> 04:14.324
There will be nothing left.

04:14.326 --> 04:15.858
So what they think of you,

04:15.860 --> 04:17.927
you can see how that might
not matter so much.

04:17.928 --> 04:19.495
It's my job.

04:19.497 --> 04:21.096
You're beautiful and talented,

04:21.099 --> 04:22.999
and I'm sure you'll land on your feet.

04:23.001 --> 04:24.733
Fuck you.

04:27.105 --> 04:30.306
Get Emi Kenyon back in here!

04:43.887 --> 04:45.320
Hello?

05:07.209 --> 05:11.510
Yesterday, this company
came under attack

05:11.512 --> 05:14.480
by an unscrupulous adversary

05:14.482 --> 05:16.850
who will stop at nothing

05:16.852 --> 05:18.952
to abuse the authority of the state,

05:18.954 --> 05:20.686
take away our freedoms,

05:20.688 --> 05:22.621
and close our doors forever.

05:22.623 --> 05:24.089
And it left us all

05:24.091 --> 05:26.225
wondering one thing...

05:26.227 --> 05:29.494
- What happens next?

05:33.968 --> 05:37.802
Dollar Bill Stearn.

05:37.804 --> 05:40.238
Stingiest multimillionaire
on the planet.

05:41.707 --> 05:43.741
Better get ready to pay full price.

05:47.513 --> 05:49.413
Insider trading, securities fraud,

05:49.415 --> 05:52.549
conspiracy, wire fraud.
What are we up to?

05:52.551 --> 05:54.285
Uh, 12-year prison term.

05:54.287 --> 05:55.486
Mm.

05:55.488 --> 05:56.653
$9 million fine,

05:56.655 --> 05:58.889
plus civil when it moves to SEC.

05:58.891 --> 06:02.025
Jesus, that's pricey, and
that's just the beginning.

06:02.027 --> 06:04.261
They came for Dollar Bill yesterday,

06:04.263 --> 06:07.197
but it was an attack on all of us.

06:07.199 --> 06:08.431
- Right. Right.
- Yeah.

06:08.433 --> 06:09.565
- That's right.
- Yeah.

06:09.567 --> 06:11.434
- And I feel it. Do you?
- Uh-huh.

06:11.436 --> 06:12.769
Yeah.

06:12.771 --> 06:14.003
Any one of us could be next.

06:14.005 --> 06:15.504
We're with you, Bobby!

06:15.506 --> 06:17.139
Yeah!

06:21.946 --> 06:23.512
Do you think this makes me happy, Bill?

06:23.514 --> 06:25.281
You don't need to answer that.

06:25.283 --> 06:26.581
- You happy, Bryan?
- Yeah, I'm...

06:26.583 --> 06:27.783
Right?

06:27.785 --> 06:29.985
It doesn't feel right.
It doesn't feel fair.

06:29.987 --> 06:34.455
Why you? Why are you
sitting in that chair...

06:34.457 --> 06:35.823
and not somebody else?

06:35.825 --> 06:38.293
Today...

06:38.295 --> 06:41.129
we are standing at the precipice.

06:41.131 --> 06:43.697
Today is one day after.

06:43.699 --> 06:48.402
You have one chance to avoid a cell.

06:48.404 --> 06:50.170
Give me Axelrod.

06:52.207 --> 06:55.008
The day after Pearl Harbor,

06:55.010 --> 06:57.644
everybody knew a Japanese
invasion would be coming.

06:57.646 --> 07:00.680
Air raid wardens.
Anti-aircraft artillery.

07:00.682 --> 07:02.215
Cities blacked out.

07:02.217 --> 07:04.984
Mothers and fathers staying by the door

07:04.986 --> 07:08.254
with baseball bats and kitchen knives,

07:08.256 --> 07:12.058
bellies full of fear of
the invading hordes.

07:12.060 --> 07:14.726
I know what he means to you.

07:14.728 --> 07:18.797
I know you're a loyal
man, and I admire that.

07:18.799 --> 07:22.500
But this is what you know.

07:22.502 --> 07:26.204
You know he's crooked, and
you know he's going down.

07:26.206 --> 07:28.974
But everyone was wrong.

07:28.976 --> 07:31.176
What happened on American soil next?

07:31.178 --> 07:32.577
Nothing.

07:32.579 --> 07:34.346
That's right.

07:34.348 --> 07:36.014
The invasion never came.

07:36.016 --> 07:37.148
Turned out Pearl Harbor was the best

07:37.150 --> 07:39.049
those sneak attacking
motherfuckers had.

07:41.920 --> 07:44.788
I have the men. I have the tools.

07:44.790 --> 07:47.458
I have the will.

07:47.460 --> 07:49.994
Now if it's not you,
it'll be someone else.

07:49.996 --> 07:52.429
I'll go through your
shop, one PM at a time,

07:52.431 --> 07:54.098
pick up every piece of rotten fruit

07:54.100 --> 07:56.732
and squeeze until the juice comes out.

07:56.734 --> 07:59.102
You know.

07:59.104 --> 08:01.437
You know.

08:01.439 --> 08:04.207
So you can cooperate and
walk out of here free,

08:04.209 --> 08:07.477
or you can go to jail
for no good reason.

08:09.414 --> 08:12.281
You have one chance to make this deal.

08:12.283 --> 08:14.483
A deal won't be on the table tomorrow.

08:14.485 --> 08:18.220
What came next was a war

08:18.222 --> 08:21.056
that unleashed the might of America.

08:21.058 --> 08:24.759
What came next was a
victory that left us

08:24.761 --> 08:26.961
as the most powerful nation on Earth.

08:26.963 --> 08:27.996
Fuck, yeah!

08:33.602 --> 08:36.270
No deal.

08:36.272 --> 08:39.407
This company...

08:39.409 --> 08:43.110
This company will not wait
for an uncertain future.

08:43.111 --> 08:46.147
We will make our own future!

08:46.149 --> 08:49.249
We will fight back hard.

08:49.251 --> 08:51.484
We will mobilize the war machine.

08:51.486 --> 08:53.853
And those who would try
to bring down our house

08:53.855 --> 08:55.821
will see their own houses fall!

09:10.204 --> 09:13.972
The case against my client
is entirely without merit.

09:16.410 --> 09:21.946
Bill Stearn bribed a company official

09:21.948 --> 09:24.415
in exchange for material
inside information.

09:24.417 --> 09:27.218
It does not get any clearer.

09:27.220 --> 09:31.622
He became friends with a farmer
working at a company he covers.

09:31.624 --> 09:35.159
He was so moved by the plight
of that man's daughter

09:35.161 --> 09:38.795
that he arranged transportation
and medical care for her.

09:38.797 --> 09:41.431
Now if you can convince
a jury of citizens

09:41.433 --> 09:44.434
that paying to save the
life of a sick child

09:44.436 --> 09:47.036
constitutes an illegal benefit,

09:47.038 --> 09:49.206
then you should go ahead
and take us to trial.

09:52.411 --> 09:54.844
My client has no
interest in cooperation,

09:54.846 --> 09:57.313
no interest in a plea...

10:02.820 --> 10:06.788
And he does not recognize
your authority.

10:08.993 --> 10:11.760
What the fuck does that mean?

10:14.864 --> 10:17.765
Liquidate 2% of the fund immediately.

10:17.767 --> 10:19.066
That's our war chest.

10:19.068 --> 10:22.103
$300 million. Nice rack.
Legal defense is paid for.

10:22.105 --> 10:23.704
How many billions are out the door

10:23.706 --> 10:25.039
at the first redemption?

10:25.041 --> 10:27.175
You should gate the whole damn fund

10:27.177 --> 10:28.676
before they start a run on...

10:41.123 --> 10:43.957
We're fucked.

10:43.959 --> 10:46.159
That's not the impression
you gave out there.

10:46.161 --> 10:47.527
Pretty tough talk.

10:47.529 --> 10:49.162
You think I'm overreacting?

10:49.164 --> 10:52.498
I think... open war isn't good.

10:52.500 --> 10:54.500
- For who?
- For anyone.

10:59.307 --> 11:03.142
I think your whole mentality
right now is a mistake.

11:03.144 --> 11:04.242
You're not accepting

11:04.244 --> 11:05.877
that certain things are
out of your control.

11:05.879 --> 11:07.145
Damn right I'm not.

11:07.147 --> 11:10.248
And it's causing you
to lose more control.

11:10.250 --> 11:12.617
If you wanna get it back, if you
really wanna survive this thing,

11:12.619 --> 11:15.520
then you may need to set aside
the piece of you that's...

11:15.522 --> 11:18.223
raging, and do something

11:18.225 --> 11:19.857
that makes you a little uncomfortable.

11:27.400 --> 11:29.600
- He's not gonna flip?
- No, he will,

11:29.602 --> 11:32.869
because you're gonna make it happen.
All of you.

11:32.871 --> 11:35.506
Everything you have on
him, get underneath it.

11:35.508 --> 11:37.174
Not the what... the why.

11:37.176 --> 11:40.009
What motivates him. Fears. Goals.

11:40.011 --> 11:41.444
Scars.

11:41.446 --> 11:45.215
He has a weak point, and we
need to twist a knife in it.

11:45.217 --> 11:47.383
Is there something else?

11:47.385 --> 11:49.686
We know how Axelrod's operation works.

11:49.688 --> 11:51.087
He keeps himself insulated.

11:51.089 --> 11:52.388
Is there a point you're trying to make?

11:52.390 --> 11:54.789
Some random PM at Axe Cap
isn't gonna have the goods.

11:54.791 --> 11:57.125
We need inner circle. Bill
Stearn is our best shot.

11:57.127 --> 11:59.328
Is this something you
think I don't understand?

11:59.330 --> 12:01.096
Hey, I just don't want Axe to walk away

12:01.098 --> 12:03.865
with a fine and a family
office like Birch.

12:03.867 --> 12:08.002
Is that what you think I'm doing? No.

12:08.004 --> 12:10.004
Axe is no ordinary billionaire.

12:10.006 --> 12:12.506
He's not Steven fucking Birch.

12:12.508 --> 12:15.776
He's an icon of the wealth of our age,

12:15.778 --> 12:18.346
and he is a fraud.

12:18.348 --> 12:21.682
So when he falls, he's
gonna hit the ground hard.

12:21.684 --> 12:24.619
Skilling got 14 years for Enron.
I'm gonna beat that.

12:24.621 --> 12:27.221
I just wanna take this one to
trial, let the jury decide.

12:27.223 --> 12:30.823
We're gonna put him in a cell,
and everyone is gonna see...

12:30.825 --> 12:33.993
in Washington, in the fucking press...

12:33.995 --> 12:35.562
there's no better defender
of the public trust

12:35.564 --> 12:37.163
than this office.

12:37.165 --> 12:39.165
They'll say Chuck Rhoades did that,

12:39.167 --> 12:41.501
and no one is out of his reach.

12:41.503 --> 12:45.704
You're damn skippy they will.

12:59.052 --> 13:00.286
Lara.

13:00.288 --> 13:01.853
You shouldn't be here.

13:01.855 --> 13:05.089
Come in quickly. I think
they're watching the house.

13:09.095 --> 13:11.195
They went through everything.

13:11.197 --> 13:14.064
They broke Bill's home office...
the door, in half.

13:14.066 --> 13:16.734
And I was getting the key.
Look at this.

13:16.736 --> 13:18.736
All our accounts are frozen.

13:18.738 --> 13:20.537
They didn't even wipe their feet.

13:20.539 --> 13:23.440
Sandy, stay strong, okay?

13:23.442 --> 13:25.175
It's a difficult time for everyone.

13:27.913 --> 13:31.047
You brought muffins?

13:45.363 --> 13:46.895
This is your mortgage, property tax,

13:46.897 --> 13:49.965
insurance, school tuition, and
that's for your foundation.

13:49.967 --> 13:53.668
Everything is taken care of,
for as long as this lasts.

13:53.670 --> 13:56.971
Thank you. Thank you so much.

14:08.352 --> 14:09.484
Here.

14:09.486 --> 14:11.485
Want a taste?

14:12.755 --> 14:14.388
It's like whiskey dipped
in milk chocolate.

14:15.825 --> 14:17.491
Are we celebrating something?

14:17.493 --> 14:22.095
Mm-hmm. I want to apologize.

14:22.097 --> 14:25.499
I was a big, puckered
asshole yesterday.

14:25.501 --> 14:27.734
I had no right to talk to you that way.

14:27.736 --> 14:29.802
I'll drink to that.

14:41.949 --> 14:43.215
Oh, wow.

14:43.217 --> 14:45.384
Right?

14:45.386 --> 14:49.588
Yeah, the Taiwanese do it better
than the Scots these days.

14:51.091 --> 14:53.925
How would you talk to me?

14:53.927 --> 14:57.829
If you had a do-over.

14:57.831 --> 14:59.765
What would you say?

14:59.767 --> 15:01.299
I don't want to have this fight again.

15:01.301 --> 15:03.267
Then let's not fight. Let's talk.

15:03.269 --> 15:06.103
No posturing. No bullshit.

15:06.105 --> 15:07.638
Okay.

15:08.674 --> 15:11.041
Right.

15:11.043 --> 15:12.743
What do you want to know?

15:12.745 --> 15:16.447
Why are you going after him so hard?
Why Axe?

15:16.449 --> 15:19.282
For the same reason my
office does anything.

15:19.284 --> 15:21.818
He broke the law. He cheated.

15:21.820 --> 15:23.653
Then why you?

15:23.655 --> 15:26.790
How many cases are you this
involved with personally?

15:28.427 --> 15:29.926
I don't know. Uh, four, five.

15:29.928 --> 15:31.761
Why does this have to be one of them?

15:31.763 --> 15:34.163
Why don't you recuse yourself?

15:34.165 --> 15:35.497
- Out of the question.
- Why?

15:35.499 --> 15:37.933
Because I owe it to my team.
I owe it to the public.

15:37.935 --> 15:40.001
It's my responsibility to prosecute.

15:40.003 --> 15:43.338
It doesn't have to be you.

15:43.340 --> 15:44.973
Give the case to Bryan Connerty alone,

15:44.975 --> 15:46.875
or the Eastern District.

15:46.877 --> 15:50.412
This case?

15:50.414 --> 15:54.148
SEC, Eastern, uh, State AG...

15:54.150 --> 15:58.319
they have been whispering about
Axelrod for years, waiting.

15:58.321 --> 15:59.821
I'm the one that stood up.

15:59.823 --> 16:01.823
I'm the only one that did something.

16:01.825 --> 16:04.158
This is an action against me.

16:04.160 --> 16:05.526
Do you understand?

16:05.528 --> 16:09.129
Do you? Because this
is bigger than you.

16:09.131 --> 16:10.630
It's bigger than me.

16:10.632 --> 16:13.934
He runs more money than the
GDP of a European nation.

16:13.936 --> 16:17.671
He's untouchable, and I
have him dead to rights.

16:17.673 --> 16:19.773
You may think you do, but you don't.

16:19.775 --> 16:21.958
Really? What makes you so sure?

16:22.043 --> 16:23.843
Because...

16:24.045 --> 16:25.411
I have never seen him like this.

16:25.413 --> 16:28.481
He is digging trenches and laying wire,

16:28.483 --> 16:30.950
and he will scorch the
earth under our feet.

16:30.952 --> 16:32.317
Tell me more about what he's doing.

16:32.319 --> 16:33.619
I can't go further.

16:33.621 --> 16:36.655
And it's wrong of you to push.
I took an oath.

16:36.657 --> 16:40.058
Me, too. And that's why
I can't recuse myself.

16:40.060 --> 16:42.294
Yes, you can.

16:42.296 --> 16:43.495
You just won't.

16:55.942 --> 16:58.376
Ahh.

17:30.642 --> 17:33.509
We've gone down this road,
backwards and sideways.

17:33.511 --> 17:35.176
Now we gotta do it on
our hands and knees.

17:35.178 --> 17:36.411
That's a fun image.

17:36.413 --> 17:37.846
I don't even know what
we're looking for anymore.

17:37.848 --> 17:40.415
He's gotta be hiding something.

17:40.417 --> 17:43.018
I've never seen anybody
so clean in his world.

17:43.020 --> 17:44.118
Ah, except for, you know,

17:44.120 --> 17:45.654
the bribery and securities fraud.

17:45.656 --> 17:47.288
Ah, he might not think it's illegal.

17:47.290 --> 17:50.391
He might be right. The courts
keep moving the goalposts.

17:50.393 --> 17:51.526
Yeah, I know what they tell themselves.

17:51.528 --> 17:54.028
I've been to those
Sohn conferences, too.

17:54.030 --> 17:57.164
"Capitalism is under siege."

17:57.166 --> 18:01.035
All those guys think if you can't
prove they did the murder,

18:01.037 --> 18:02.903
then they're not a killer.

18:02.905 --> 18:05.105
Don't fucking kid yourself.

18:05.107 --> 18:07.207
They're only players 'cause
they rigged the game.

18:07.209 --> 18:08.308
Of course.

18:10.812 --> 18:12.845
Huh?

18:14.716 --> 18:17.050
Hmm? That's all I got.

18:18.086 --> 18:20.086
Greedy or cheap, it's a fine line.

18:20.088 --> 18:21.821
What are his greatest hits, Terri?

18:21.823 --> 18:26.291
Uh, reusing paper towels. $1
taco night at Acapulco's.

18:26.293 --> 18:28.359
No Benz, no Audi.

18:28.361 --> 18:31.396
Just two identical Honda minivans.

18:31.398 --> 18:33.498
Who the fuck has two minivans?

18:33.500 --> 18:36.167
- One in beige, one in...
- boring.

18:36.169 --> 18:38.436
Nobody.

18:39.840 --> 18:42.673
Nobody has two minivans. That's it.

18:42.675 --> 18:44.341
There's something there, and
we need to find out what.

18:45.745 --> 18:49.480
We're gonna bleed out.

18:49.482 --> 18:51.115
We'll be a family office
by the end of the year,

18:51.117 --> 18:52.617
by SEC mandate or not.

18:52.619 --> 18:53.918
We need to take action.

18:53.920 --> 18:55.452
We need to cut through the chatter.

18:55.454 --> 18:56.754
We need to get it out there...

18:56.756 --> 18:58.956
Rhoades has no case, he'll
be laughed out of court.

18:58.958 --> 19:00.556
You know that doesn't matter.

19:00.558 --> 19:02.125
The smoke is enough to choke you.

19:02.127 --> 19:03.426
There doesn't need to be a fire.

