34:22.292 --> 34:25.726
Mm.

34:30.367 --> 34:32.801
Getting him to take the plea deal...

34:32.803 --> 34:35.469
that's the trick.

34:35.472 --> 34:38.138
A big settlement that'll hurt him,

34:38.139 --> 34:39.607
get him off of outside money.

34:39.609 --> 34:41.440
What makes you think I would settle?

34:41.443 --> 34:43.610
My desktop calendar.

34:43.612 --> 34:46.079
A conviction could take years.

34:46.081 --> 34:48.447
You don't want it to be your
successor that gets the credit.

34:48.449 --> 34:52.952
No, I'll be on the podium for this.

34:52.954 --> 34:57.557
Son, has your vision
of the future changed?

34:57.559 --> 34:59.826
Or is it just my vision?

34:59.828 --> 35:02.929
Because after... after that
short squeeze incident...

35:02.931 --> 35:05.264
and I understand that I put
you in a bad position.

35:05.266 --> 35:06.566
I understand that.

35:07.769 --> 35:11.570
Your performance left me
more convinced than ever

35:11.572 --> 35:13.939
of your greatness.

35:13.941 --> 35:18.577
There is no high office in the
land you could not attain.

35:18.579 --> 35:21.680
- Okay, Dad, I appreciate...
- But if you want that,

35:21.682 --> 35:25.383
you have to think about
things in a certain way.

35:25.385 --> 35:29.053
I didn't when I was
younger, and it cost me.

35:29.055 --> 35:31.656
You can't allow yourself

35:31.658 --> 35:35.826
to get drawn in to an unwinnable fight.

35:35.828 --> 35:38.395
And I won't.

35:38.397 --> 35:41.098
Victory will be swift, Dad.

35:41.100 --> 35:45.201
No. Be realistic.

35:45.203 --> 35:47.437
This guy is gearing up...

35:47.439 --> 35:49.172
...for trench warfare.

35:55.547 --> 35:57.647
You've been talking to
Wendy, haven't you?

36:00.518 --> 36:03.118
Well, you're the one
who's always telling me

36:03.120 --> 36:06.521
that she has your best
interests at heart.

36:15.532 --> 36:17.532
What the hell was that?

36:17.534 --> 36:20.434
You've twisted my father into
carrying your water now?

36:20.436 --> 36:23.537
He called. I told him what I think.

36:23.539 --> 36:25.106
He agreed with me.

36:25.108 --> 36:28.209
That I should settle, huh?

36:30.981 --> 36:33.014
Nice try.

36:33.016 --> 36:36.149
You want me to think that, uh,
you're trying to save your job?

36:36.151 --> 36:37.784
Really, you're trying to save Axelrod.

36:37.786 --> 36:40.787
I am trying to save you

36:40.789 --> 36:42.723
and me and him...

36:42.725 --> 36:44.791
- and your father.

36:47.229 --> 36:49.496
Do you trust me?

36:52.266 --> 36:53.866
Just because I trust you

36:53.868 --> 36:57.637
doesn't mean I think you're right.

36:57.639 --> 37:01.373
Ask me anything.

37:01.375 --> 37:03.943
Are you gonna open up
the book on Axe for me?

37:03.945 --> 37:05.544
The whole way?

37:05.546 --> 37:09.047
- What about the oath?
- What do you want to know?

37:09.049 --> 37:10.414
What's he thinking right now?
What's he doing?

37:10.416 --> 37:12.684
He's looking for a win.

37:12.686 --> 37:15.887
Always. He needs to find
at least a small win

37:15.889 --> 37:18.256
in every endeavor, every exchange.

37:18.258 --> 37:19.791
What happens if he can't find one?

37:19.793 --> 37:21.926
Then he'll play a different game,

37:21.928 --> 37:23.327
with different rules...
ones you don't know,

37:23.329 --> 37:25.996
no one knows, where...

37:25.998 --> 37:28.899
he can make your loss
bigger than his loss.

37:28.901 --> 37:32.069
A lose-lose scenario. And
that doesn't bother him?

37:32.071 --> 37:34.838
Of course it does, but
Axe came from nothing.

37:34.840 --> 37:36.606
So unconsciously, he fears...

37:36.608 --> 37:41.779
No, he may even expect
he'll have nothing again.

37:41.781 --> 37:44.413
So he...

37:44.415 --> 37:50.486
loves to put that same
fear into others,

37:50.488 --> 37:52.521
especially if they're
not familiar with it.

38:00.164 --> 38:02.764
Like the Eads family.

38:02.766 --> 38:04.666
The naming rights? I heard about that.

38:04.668 --> 38:07.936
But that's just the
part of him I know...

38:07.938 --> 38:10.538
that he's allowed me to see.

38:10.540 --> 38:12.808
But you know him better than anybody.

38:12.810 --> 38:16.277
Well, I think I do, but I'm
not really sure anyone can.

38:20.616 --> 38:22.750
He's most likely ahead of you...

38:24.687 --> 38:26.520
Especially when it looks like he's not.

38:26.522 --> 38:29.523
And if he does go down, he
will pull you down with him.

38:29.525 --> 38:31.291
I'm not afraid to prosecute anybody.

38:31.293 --> 38:32.893
Okay, it's not about that.

38:32.895 --> 38:34.660
It's about you being your alpha self,

38:34.662 --> 38:36.362
not letting him pull
you out of your game.

38:36.364 --> 38:38.932
That's his goal in all his deals...

38:38.934 --> 38:41.567
get under their skin, get
them to make a mistake.

38:43.905 --> 38:47.907
If this was a different
case, uh, at this stage,

38:47.909 --> 38:50.809
I would pursue a plea agreement.

38:50.811 --> 38:53.078
You would.

38:53.080 --> 38:55.047
It's a cardinal rule... you
don't trust your career

38:55.049 --> 38:59.084
in the hands of a jury of
12 random crazy people

38:59.086 --> 39:01.519
who might decide a case
based on a wink and a smile

39:01.521 --> 39:04.156
and not the law,

39:04.158 --> 39:06.558
which they can't fucking
understand in the first place.

39:10.463 --> 39:12.663
Would he take a deal?

39:12.665 --> 39:15.199
He'd settle if he thought it was a win.

39:15.201 --> 39:17.268
If he thought he tricked
you, even better.

39:17.270 --> 39:18.903
The only deal with teeth

39:18.905 --> 39:21.239
would have to take him
out of business forever.

39:21.241 --> 39:22.974
That's the only deal
he would never take.

39:22.976 --> 39:26.542
Would he take a family office?
Would he admit guilt?

39:26.544 --> 39:28.078
Why don't you ask his lawyer?

39:28.080 --> 39:31.314
No, they have to come to me.

39:31.316 --> 39:36.319
If they come to me,
then it's on my terms.

39:36.321 --> 39:39.956
I can get him to come to you.

39:39.958 --> 39:42.624
Are you sure?

39:42.626 --> 39:43.793
I mean...

39:43.795 --> 39:46.796
what if the Axe we're
dealing with now...

39:46.798 --> 39:49.298
What if that's the part of
him you don't know about?

40:07.884 --> 40:09.918
What happened?

40:09.920 --> 40:12.954
Well, Lawrence Boyd
sent me the message.

40:12.956 --> 40:15.956
He pissed right in my face.

40:22.031 --> 40:24.832
Holy shit. Bobby Axelrod!

40:24.834 --> 40:27.234
Can I get a selfie? I'll get
mad followers on my Instagram.

40:27.236 --> 40:28.969
He didn't show.

40:28.971 --> 40:32.639
The room was full of
20-year-old dipshits.

40:32.641 --> 40:34.173
It was mailroom night.

40:39.080 --> 40:41.413
Well, what the hell do we do now?

40:43.584 --> 40:44.717
It's worse than I thought.

40:44.719 --> 40:46.552
That's why we're standing here.

40:46.554 --> 40:48.520
I didn't think it would go like this,

40:48.522 --> 40:52.257
this fast.

40:52.259 --> 40:53.291
What's the counter?

40:53.293 --> 40:54.759
It's easy.

40:54.761 --> 40:58.363
Rhoades is vulnerable, exposed.

40:58.365 --> 41:01.799
Conflict of interest.

41:01.801 --> 41:03.201
Wendy.

41:03.203 --> 41:06.571
I make it look like she's involved.

41:06.573 --> 41:09.139
Fraud, embezzlement.

41:09.141 --> 41:10.574
Or maybe she's having an affair...

41:10.576 --> 41:14.245
with Bill Stearn.

41:14.247 --> 41:16.981
With you, even.

41:16.983 --> 41:19.884
Watch how fast the case goes away.

41:21.754 --> 41:24.120
I'll let you know.

41:29.094 --> 41:31.127
He's working out of the office today.

41:31.129 --> 41:32.661
Will you tell him I need to talk?

41:32.663 --> 41:34.663
In person. It's important.

41:34.665 --> 41:37.633
Of course.

41:37.635 --> 41:39.168
You're gonna give him a deal?

41:39.170 --> 41:40.870
You're gonna fucking let him walk?

41:40.872 --> 41:43.505
If Axelrod comes to the table,
we'll see what we can get.

41:43.507 --> 41:44.839
It's the smart way to go.

41:44.841 --> 41:48.043
That's not what you said two days ago.
What happened?

41:48.045 --> 41:50.379
I changed my mind.

41:50.381 --> 41:54.116
Y... Ah, this is fucking
Birch all over again.

41:54.118 --> 41:56.584
I didn't come here and
sacrifice real money

41:56.586 --> 41:57.719
to let these guys write

41:57.721 --> 41:59.520
their own "get out of jail free" cards.

41:59.522 --> 42:02.223
Was it... Is that all just
bullshit posturing? Why?!

42:02.225 --> 42:03.958
Because you don't have him!

42:06.495 --> 42:07.995
Give me more time.

42:09.465 --> 42:12.666
And I will build this case
into a fucking guillotine

42:12.668 --> 42:14.035
and drop the blade.

42:14.037 --> 42:15.635
It's too late. We went into his house

42:15.637 --> 42:20.340
and, uh... we shit the bed.

42:20.342 --> 42:22.976
Every day I don't bring
charges, we lose leverage,

42:22.978 --> 42:24.477
and the deal gets better for him.

42:24.479 --> 42:26.980
So, uh, take the rest of the day off.

42:26.982 --> 42:28.648
Or better yet, wait by the phone

42:28.650 --> 42:32.117
for his people to reach out.

42:41.628 --> 42:42.894
Hello, Wendy.

42:46.167 --> 42:47.566
Have we met?

42:47.568 --> 42:51.002
No. And we still haven't.

42:51.004 --> 42:54.138
If you wanna talk to him, get in.

42:57.577 --> 42:58.709
Where are we going?

43:20.032 --> 43:22.799
We have to take precautions.

43:22.801 --> 43:25.201
There's a protocol.

43:38.149 --> 43:41.349
It's been a weird couple of days.

43:41.351 --> 43:43.551
Yeah.

43:43.553 --> 43:46.687
It's hard to be sure about anything...

43:46.689 --> 43:48.289
anyone.

43:48.291 --> 43:51.292
I understand.

43:51.294 --> 43:55.730
I need to understand something, too.

43:55.732 --> 43:59.033
That's why we're sitting
here like this.

43:59.035 --> 44:00.367
No one listening but us.

44:03.906 --> 44:07.974
Have I won your trust?

44:07.976 --> 44:10.110
What do you want to understand?

44:10.112 --> 44:13.980
Why are you sticking around?

44:17.985 --> 44:20.853
I am interested in what
that question means to you.

44:20.855 --> 44:22.788
I wanna know...

44:22.790 --> 44:27.893
No, I know, I... you just
wanna hear my answer.

44:27.895 --> 44:32.397
I'm not gonna tell you I'm
staying because you need me.

44:32.399 --> 44:35.467
Even though you do, more than ever.

44:35.469 --> 44:37.436
And I'm not gonna tell you
I'm here for my patients

44:37.438 --> 44:41.005
or because I love my job,
even though I do love my job.

44:41.007 --> 44:44.943
And your collection of
insecure egomaniacs

44:44.945 --> 44:46.445
would lose a billion a year

44:46.447 --> 44:49.113
if I didn't keep their heads straight.

44:49.115 --> 44:53.417
And I am not going to tell you
I'm here spying for Chuck,

44:53.419 --> 44:57.788
Because you know that's
total fucking nonsense.

45:01.461 --> 45:02.726
The answer...

45:05.163 --> 45:09.566
My answer is, I'm here for me.

45:09.568 --> 45:12.335
Because I built this company
just as much as you did.

45:12.337 --> 45:14.270
That's a bold statement.

45:14.272 --> 45:16.906
That's a true statement.

45:16.908 --> 45:19.742
I put you back together again

45:19.744 --> 45:21.944
when your whole world burned.

45:26.484 --> 45:29.985
And I found meaning in that.

45:29.987 --> 45:31.886
I still do.

45:31.888 --> 45:34.089
I'm not...

45:34.091 --> 45:37.892
happy here, not always. Not... now.

45:41.097 --> 45:44.499
But meaning matters more
to me than happiness.

45:44.501 --> 45:49.504
And I am in this water

45:49.506 --> 45:51.005
because I don't want to see
you throw it all anyway

45:51.007 --> 45:52.240
when you don't have to.

45:52.242 --> 45:54.342
I know.

45:57.679 --> 45:59.412
And I don't want us to lose you.

46:10.725 --> 46:13.492
I wanna make a deal. Will he make one?

46:13.494 --> 46:16.028
- Yes.
- Will I be able to live with it?

46:19.233 --> 46:21.733
That's up to you.

46:21.735 --> 46:23.769
That has nothing to do with the deal.

46:38.084 --> 46:40.351
How do you feel?

46:40.353 --> 46:42.086
Like somebody else.

46:44.558 --> 46:46.357
What am I gonna say about it?

46:49.695 --> 46:52.128
That I did the right thing.

46:56.468 --> 46:58.702
For all of us.

47:06.877 --> 47:09.278
Adam, hi.

47:09.280 --> 47:13.349
Uh, just wanted to thank you
for stopping by the other day.

47:13.351 --> 47:17.520
I thought about what you said,
and I'm not gonna recuse myself.

47:17.522 --> 47:20.223
Well, that's unfortunate.

47:20.225 --> 47:22.123
I believe the Greeks
call that hamartia.

47:22.125 --> 47:23.758
I disagree,

47:23.760 --> 47:26.528
because I'm not gonna lose, and
there will not be an appeal.

47:26.530 --> 47:28.996
Axelrod surrendered.

47:28.998 --> 47:30.398
What? A deal?

47:30.400 --> 47:32.400
Mm-hmm. Yeah, we have
a deal on the table,

47:32.402 --> 47:36.438
a termination, a plea,
and $1.9 billion.

47:37.974 --> 47:40.307
Biggest insider fine ever paid.

47:40.309 --> 47:42.175
Anyway, thanks again.

47:42.177 --> 47:44.077
Give my regards to the maestro.

47:44.079 --> 47:46.580
You got it, Chuck. Good job.

47:51.220 --> 47:54.154
Your father's still holding
on the other line.

47:57.425 --> 47:58.891
Dad, hello.

47:58.893 --> 48:02.662
Chuckie boy, I heard. I
heard you took him down.

48:02.664 --> 48:06.299
I'm, uh, I'm smoking a
cigar for you right now...

48:06.301 --> 48:07.800
as soon as I get outside.

48:07.802 --> 48:09.469
I'm not supposed to
in the house now that

48:09.471 --> 48:10.770
your mother heard Wendy's rule.

48:10.772 --> 48:13.672
But congratulations!

48:13.674 --> 48:15.574
Yeah, we're quite happy with the terms.

48:15.576 --> 48:17.576
- Well, it's the smart play.
- Yeah.

48:17.578 --> 48:19.844
And even as a kid, you would
never get into a fight

48:19.846 --> 48:21.680
unless you knew you could win it.

48:21.682 --> 48:25.884
Oh, do you remember that Mintz boy?

48:25.886 --> 48:27.552
He was a head taller than you,

48:27.554 --> 48:29.020
probably could've made you eat dirt.

48:29.022 --> 48:32.156
And he left that ball field
thinking you were best friends.

48:32.158 --> 48:33.491
Okay, Dad, I gotta go.

48:33.493 --> 48:36.126
And then I made sure he
didn't get into Dalton.

48:36.128 --> 48:37.728
Goodbye!

48:41.167 --> 48:42.933
Highest fucking fine ever levied...

48:42.935 --> 48:44.769
$1.9 billion.

48:44.771 --> 48:46.036
We got everything we wanted.

48:46.038 --> 48:47.537
Family office. Sure.

48:47.539 --> 48:48.971
- Yeah.
- That's worse

48:48.973 --> 48:51.174
than the fucking fine.

48:51.176 --> 48:53.610
The money I can get
back, but not my name.

48:53.612 --> 48:55.578
We'll petition for reinstatement,

48:55.580 --> 48:59.081
after Rhoades leaves, after
the White House turns over.

48:59.083 --> 49:00.483
We'll get it.

49:00.485 --> 49:03.585
You'll be managing outside
money again within five years.

49:03.587 --> 49:07.456
That's five years I'll never get back.

49:07.458 --> 49:08.657
Where's the silverware?

49:08.659 --> 49:11.427
No, it's, uh, it's Ethiopian.

49:11.429 --> 49:15.163
I got you extra injera, and,
uh, you use your hands.

49:18.669 --> 49:22.169
This is an opportunity
to be here with us.

49:22.171 --> 49:24.372
Step it up, Ben Kim.

49:24.374 --> 49:26.674
Step... it... up.

49:26.676 --> 49:29.544
Sorry. I'll go... I'll go get some.

49:29.546 --> 49:31.346
You have it?

49:31.348 --> 49:33.581
Right here.

49:51.500 --> 49:54.234
Uh... there's one other thing.

49:54.236 --> 49:56.168
I do not like other things.

49:56.170 --> 49:59.938
I sensed a possible waffle on
the specifics of the plea.

49:59.940 --> 50:02.341
Connerty did commit to a no guilty plea

50:02.343 --> 50:05.411
but said he would have to
reconfirm with Rhoades.

50:05.413 --> 50:07.279
What could they come with?

50:07.281 --> 50:10.783
At worst, the company will have
to plead guilty to conspiracy.

50:10.785 --> 50:12.817
- Fuck.
- Penalty is the same.

50:12.819 --> 50:14.586
An admission of guilt?

50:17.190 --> 50:20.425
If they put that in
front of me tomorrow,

50:20.427 --> 50:22.894
I don't think I can sign it.

50:35.274 --> 50:36.707
It's gonna be okay.

50:36.709 --> 50:39.042
Mm.

51:06.236 --> 51:08.437
They're coming up.

51:28.190 --> 51:30.023
You've been briefed by
your lawyers, Mr. Axelrod.

51:30.025 --> 51:33.226
We'll try to get you out of
here as soon as possible.

51:33.228 --> 51:36.729
"As part of the proposed
global resolution,

51:36.731 --> 51:39.766
the defendant agrees to an
aggregate financial penalty

51:39.768 --> 51:42.401
of $1.9 billion.

51:42.403 --> 51:45.572
To the termination of their
investment advisory business

51:45.574 --> 51:47.674
and...

51:47.676 --> 51:51.243
the company agrees to plead
guilty to conspiracy."

52:00.287 --> 52:02.354
Do we have a deal, Mr. Axelrod?

52:15.869 --> 52:18.669
Okay.

52:18.671 --> 52:20.905
Okay.

52:20.907 --> 52:23.774
Axe Capital accepts such a penalty as

52:23.776 --> 52:26.210
fair, reasonable, and adequate
within the limitations

52:26.212 --> 52:28.945
Congress has imposed
on federal regulators

52:28.947 --> 52:31.147
to recover investor losses.

52:31.149 --> 52:34.651
Bryan...

52:34.653 --> 52:38.454
didn't he say that he
would never settle?

52:38.456 --> 52:40.557
That's what he's been saying.

52:40.559 --> 52:42.959
You know, out there, you
guys always talk so tough,

52:42.961 --> 52:46.094
but you always end up in here.

52:46.096 --> 52:48.664
Why is that?

52:48.666 --> 52:51.667
Because he knows he's a crook.

52:51.669 --> 52:54.003
Innocent people would never
take a hit like that.

52:54.005 --> 52:55.604
Beyond the pale. My client...

52:55.606 --> 52:57.773
You got me, Rhoades.

52:57.775 --> 52:59.708
$1.9 billion.

52:59.710 --> 53:01.876
It's gonna hurt.

53:01.878 --> 53:04.412
But not... not like a shark bite.

53:04.414 --> 53:06.748
It's more like a... what? A bee sting.

53:06.750 --> 53:10.018
Bee sting? No, that hurts.
More like a horse-fly.

53:10.020 --> 53:11.686
One of those little green horse-flies?

53:11.688 --> 53:12.987
Yeah, a nasty nip.

53:12.989 --> 53:15.322
No, more like an ant. Like a red ant.

53:15.324 --> 53:19.927
Yeah, yeah. Stings for a minute
but doesn't ruin the picnic.

53:19.929 --> 53:22.863
"Plea Agreement is subject
to judicial approval,

53:22.865 --> 53:25.065
pursuant to Rule 11

53:25.067 --> 53:28.134
of the Federal Rules of
Criminal Procedure."

53:28.136 --> 53:30.637
Actually, it's good to
get past this stuff.

53:30.639 --> 53:32.238
You know, just get it out of the way.

53:32.240 --> 53:34.908
And we can make that $1.9
back in, what, eight months?

53:34.910 --> 53:36.809
Six.

53:36.811 --> 53:39.311
The termination of Axe
Capital's advisory business

53:39.313 --> 53:41.948
closes the fund to outside investors.

53:41.950 --> 53:46.385
Yeah, you can score that one for
the superstars over at the SEC.

53:46.387 --> 53:47.820
As a family office,

53:47.822 --> 53:50.389
Mr. Axelrod can invest
his personal assets...

53:50.391 --> 53:52.958
No.

53:52.960 --> 53:56.127
No family office.

53:56.129 --> 53:57.328
Lifetime ban.

54:06.740 --> 54:08.707
Put the money in a trust, fine.

54:08.709 --> 54:11.108
but you never trade securities again.

54:13.913 --> 54:17.380
Not for institutions, not
for individual investors,

54:17.382 --> 54:19.316
not even for yourself.

54:50.547 --> 54:52.881
What the fuck just happened?

55:48.502 --> 55:49.802
I heard.

55:52.405 --> 55:54.972
How did it happen?

55:54.974 --> 55:58.976
The moment came and,
uh, Axe blew a gasket.

55:58.978 --> 56:02.246
Took down the whole meeting.

56:02.248 --> 56:04.115
Tore the check up into tiny pieces.

56:04.117 --> 56:08.319
I thought he might trash
the room on his way out.

56:08.321 --> 56:11.387
Christ.

56:11.389 --> 56:14.691
We're back to this.

56:14.693 --> 56:16.492
No, it's fucking worse.

56:16.494 --> 56:19.863
I c... I can't... live in the middle.

56:19.865 --> 56:23.066
You... you won't.

56:23.068 --> 56:26.936
I've decided, for the
good of our marriage,

56:26.938 --> 56:30.973
I'm not gonna be a part of
the case going forward.

56:30.975 --> 56:33.175
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

56:33.177 --> 56:35.410
I've recused myself.

56:35.412 --> 56:37.813
I already notified Washington.

56:39.751 --> 56:43.184
- I am proud of you.
- Mm.

56:43.186 --> 56:45.787
Looking past yourself.

56:45.789 --> 56:47.021
Seeing the bigger picture.

56:47.023 --> 56:48.322
Five years ago, you wouldn't have.

56:48.324 --> 56:52.393
That... is substantial fucking growth.

56:55.966 --> 56:57.398
Mmm.

57:09.145 --> 57:12.712
I gotta go walk the dog.

57:12.714 --> 57:14.014
Mm.

57:16.051 --> 57:17.583
I'll be back.

57:22.991 --> 57:24.891
Thanks for coming out so late.

57:24.893 --> 57:26.893
Always.

57:26.895 --> 57:29.361
You're a goddamn hero

57:29.363 --> 57:30.930
for standing up to those pricks today.

57:30.932 --> 57:33.166
Okay.

57:33.168 --> 57:36.201
You can count on me to
finish what you started.

57:36.203 --> 57:38.303
I'm all in.

57:38.305 --> 57:39.604
And I'm gonna put a hurt on him

57:39.606 --> 57:40.972
that he can't buy his way out of.

57:40.974 --> 57:43.241
Good. I want you to keep me in the loop

57:43.243 --> 57:44.976
about what you're doing.

57:44.978 --> 57:48.079
But you're recusing yourself.

57:48.081 --> 57:50.481
I'm still gonna need you
to keep me informed.

57:50.483 --> 57:52.917
Then you're not really recused.

57:52.919 --> 57:56.987
I am. Officially.

57:56.989 --> 57:59.023
There can't be any trail back to me.

57:59.025 --> 58:01.491
No documents, no e-mail
chains, no witnesses.

58:01.493 --> 58:03.227
We only talk behind closed doors.

58:03.229 --> 58:05.362
I can handle this case on my own.

58:05.364 --> 58:07.864
Of course you can, but
the gloves are off.

58:07.866 --> 58:11.968
We do whatever it takes.

